DOC_LEVEL: L2
MODULE: bot
PATH: src/bot/**
DESCRIPTION: Telegram bot handlers and command routing layer

ENTRYPOINT:
- src/bot/telegram.js -> createTelegramBot() registers all commands and handlers

KEY_FILES:
- src/bot/telegram.js - Main bot factory, command registration, text handler
- src/bot/commands/index.js - Router entry point, routeCommand()
- src/bot/commands/parser.js - Command text parser, parseCommand()
- src/bot/commands/registry.js - Command registration and lookup
- src/bot/commands/validator.js - Parameter validation
- src/bot/commands/formatter.js - Error message formatting
- src/bot/commands/help.js - Help text generation
- src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js - Individual command handlers

SUBDIRS:
- src/bot/commands -> command routing and dispatch
- src/bot/commands/handlers -> individual command implementations

INTERFACES:
- Telegram Commands:
  - /start - Bot startup greeting
  - /help - Dynamic help text
  - /reset - Clear chat session
  - /screenshot - Capture desktop screenshot
  - /exec <cmd> - Execute system command
  - /pipeline [action] [target] [--type=] - Pipeline management (alias: /p)
  - /bugfix <target> - Start bugfix pipeline (alias: /b)
  - /planner [action] [target] - Planner pipeline management
  - /status [--type=feature|bugfix] - Show aggregated pipeline status (alias: /s)
  - /logs [--lines=N] [--offset=N] [--type=feature|bugfix] [--file] - View pipeline logs with pagination (alias: /l)
  - /stop [target] - Stop pipeline
  - /plan [action] [type] [version] - Plan file management (status/versions/use/rollback/validate)
  - /commit [--message="..."] [--amend] [--force] - Commit code changes with pre-commit validation (alias: /c)
  - /commits [--count=N] - View session commit history (alias: /history)
- /cd <path> - Change session working directory (F-009)
- /more - View next page of paginated output (F-009)
- /ls [path] - List directory contents (alias: /dir) (F-010)
- /tree [path] - Display directory tree structure (F-010)
- /cat <file> - View file content (F-010)
- /head [N] <file> - View first N lines of file (F-010)
- /tail [N] <file> - View last N lines of file (F-010)
- /find <pattern> - Search files by name/glob pattern (F-010)
- /upload <path> - Upload file to specified path (F-010)
- /download <file> - Download file to Telegram (F-010)
- /sysinfo - Show system information (CPU/memory/disk/network) (F-012)
- /ps - List running processes (F-012)
- /kill <pid> - Terminate process by PID (F-012)
- /monitor <set|list|remove|enable|disable> - Manage alert rules (F-012)
- /history - View command history (F-013)
- /alias <name=value> - Set/show command aliases (F-013)
- /sessions - List active sessions (F-013)
- /cron add <cron-expr> <cmd> - Add scheduled task (F-014)
- /cron add --once <datetime> <cmd> - Add one-time task (F-014)
- /jobs <list|pause|resume|delete> - Manage scheduled tasks (F-014)
- /watch <path> - Watch file/directory for changes (F-014)
- /unwatch <path> - Stop watching file/directory (F-014)

TRAPS:
- Commands require authorization via isAllowedUser()
- Large logs (>=4000 chars) sent as files
- Command parsing normalizes to lowercase
- Registry stores normalized command names
- F002-CRIT-001: Parser treats first non-option token as subcommand; validator must check if command has no subcommands and use parsed.subcommand as first positional param
- F-005: /status uses status-aggregator for aggregated status; /logs uses log-pager for pagination
- F-008: /commit requires pre-commit validation (pipeline status + test status); --amend/--force require admin + confirmation
- F-012: /kill requires admin role and confirmation; /monitor rules persisted to data/alert-rules.json
- F-013: /history shows command history; /alias stored in data/aliases.json; /sessions requires admin role
- F-014: /cron creates scheduled tasks with cron expressions; /jobs manages task lifecycle; /watch monitors file changes with debouncing

DECISIONS:
- 2026-03-12 | F-002-bot-commands | Add command routing layer with parser, registry, validator for pipeline commands
- 2026-03-12 | F-002-alias-mapping | Support command aliases /p, /b, /s, /l
- 2026-03-12 | F002-CRIT-001 | Fix positional args: validator uses parsed.subcommand as first positional when command has no subcommands
- 2026-03-12 | F-003-plan-command | Add /plan command with status/versions/use/rollback/validate subcommands for plan file management
- 2026-03-13 | F-005-status-logs | Update /status and /logs to use status-aggregator and log-pager with pagination support
- 2026-03-15 | F-008-commit-commands | Add /commit and /commits commands with pre-commit validation, session tracking, and admin confirmation for --amend/--force
- 2026-03-16 | F-009-command-executor | Add /cd and /more commands for session cwd management and paginated output viewing; add direct text mode for shell execution
- 2026-03-13 | F-010-file-manager | Add /ls, /tree, /cat, /head, /tail, /find, /upload, /download commands for file system operations with security sandbox
- 2026-03-13 | F-012-system-monitor | Add /sysinfo, /ps, /kill, /monitor commands for system monitoring and process management
- 2026-03-12 | F-013-session-context | Add /history, /alias, /sessions commands for session management and alias resolution
- 2026-03-13 | F-014-scheduled-tasks | Add /cron, /jobs, /watch, /unwatch commands for scheduled task management and file monitoring
